docs.lead_paragraph: Among the many loyal friendships formed in the class of '71 at Pierson there was not one so fervent and enduring as that between Harold Markham and Alfred Jermaine. I, on the part of Germaine, my humble self, can vouch for its unfeigned sincerity, and as for Markham, why, I would, of course, vouch even the stronger for him.
